script = ExtResource("3_f3dwx")
category = 4
text = "Silas \"King's Dog\" Redgrave III, calls himself a Redgrave despite being disowned by his father. Although Silas himself has never seen the mainland, the Redgraves are a vassal family to the Walcotts and are of Stoneblood, they are one of the few noble families that came with the Walcotts during the colonisation of Varoma. Silas is a man in his 40s but is still considered one of the best swordsmen in Varoma, using his infamous silversteel blade \"Shadow's End\". He has served as the Bulwark for 20 years as his father and grandfather have before him.

As a Redgrave, Silas was taught the ways of the mainland since his birth. He began learning the blade at age 6 and even at his young age, his talent could be clearly seen. Silas beat other noble boys a few years his senior through technique alone. At the age of 16, he was anointed as a knight by the king. As is traditional, during his ceremony he asked a maiden to dance. Silas's older brother and the heir to the Redgrave's was in love with this woman, after the ceremony, enraged his brother asked him to a duel. Silas defeated him swiftly, his brother was deeply ashamed after his defeat and decided to unsheate his sword and give up knighthood. When Silas heard his brother's sword unsheathe, he expected a surprise attack and spun to block the blade. Instead he beheaded his brother. Silas's father, despite having no other heirs, considered him not a Redgrave anymore and disowned him.

For years after this event, Silas travelled the land of Varoma and eventually found himself joining the Border Brothers, defending against the increasing raids of the Ka'luta. In a few short years he rose to the rank of Commander, the highest rank he could before he was expected to convene directly with the Bulwark, his father. As his father was rarely present on the wall, an affair that grew dissent among the Border Brothers, he was never discovered nor did he meet his father until his passing due to an illness. When the Bulwark passed away, a new one had to be elected and a grand swordsmanship tournament was held by the Border Brothers, as only one of theirs could be raised to the rank of Bulwark. The 4 men who made it to the quarter-finals could be chosen by the King and the King's Council but it is more often than not that the winner is chosen. Silas won the tournament, this is where he earned his blade \"Shadow's End\" made of silversteel. Silas was seen to exemplify the values of the Stoneland, and being of Stoneblood helped, so he was chosen to become the new Bulwark.

Silas uses an aggressive, melee fighting style, he is almost impervious to most forms of attack except something extremely heavy due to his silversteel armor and shield. As a master swordsman he can defeat most other knights on the battlefield without ever being touched. When he is fighting range combatants he typically charges using his armor and shield to absorb anything thrown at him. The only magic he fears is Blood and so when he fights Ka'luta's bloodmages he does not charge forward but instead fights among his men, surrounded by his personal guard.

During his tenure as the Bulwark, Silas has achieved great feats that spread his name far. When he is not on the wall he defends his majesty in Lastock, he has blocked countless assasination attempts by the Goblin King and Ka'luta. He will follow any order given to him by the King, as he is completely devoted to the man, once the King was drunk and ordered him to kill and skin his own horse to feed him as a joke. Silas did this unquestioningly and since then has earned the nickname \"King's Dog\". On the wall, Silas has defended the Boulder from the increasing raids of the Ka'luta. Many a time he successfully ambushed the Ka'luta on Boulder's Way, he is said to have an almost prophetic prediction of enemy movements and assasination attempts. His most notable achievement is leading a quarter of his force through the Old Road and massacring a Ka'luta outpost from behind during the night, this feat kept the Stoneroad much safer and easier to defend for years to come.

In recent years, Silas has began spending much more of his time on the wall, the Ka'luta have grown restless as K'haal grows, experimenting with more grotesque forms of blood magic. He has no time to visit the Redgrave estate he inherited after his father's passing, to visit Lastock or to form a family. Silas wishes to reestablish the Redgrave's as a significant force, he knows it will die with his passing as there are no heirs to inherit. However his duty and honor keep him on the wall, he knows that once he retires the Ka'luta will pounce at the temporary weakness of the Border Brothers as the new Bulwark establishes himself. Silas also worries that whoever is reelected will not have the strength to hold the Border Brothers together, as the position has been held by the Redgrave's since its inception. Due to all this Silas expects to hold the wall until he grows weak or dies, but yet he longs for a different life."
id = 75
name = "Silas III"
